Aim:
To write programs in C that perform AND and XOR operation with 127 on each character of 
the string "Hello World" and display the result.
Theory:
Bitwise operations such as AND (&) and XOR (^) are commonly used in cryptography and 
data security.
Properties:
A AND 127 → Clears the most significant bit (MSB)
A XOR 127 → Flips the lower 7 bits
127 in binary = 01111111
When a character is ANDed with 127, the most significate bit becomes 0.
When a character is XORed with 127, the bits of the character are inverted.
These operations are used in encryption, encoding, and data security algorithms.
Algorithm:
1. Initialize a string with value "Hello World"
2. Traverse each character in the string
3. Perform AND operation of each character with 127
4. Perform XOR operation of each character with 127
5. Display the resulting characters
6. Continue until the end of the string
C Program:
#include <stdio.h>
int main()
{
 char *str = "Hello World";
 int i = 0;
